3. Streaming implementation (`_iter_saved_papers_csv`, lines 112-131, and
   `_EchoBuffer`, lines 101-109): this is a real generator function using
   `yield` per row, backed by `csv.writer(_EchoBuffer())` where
   `_EchoBuffer.write()` returns the formatted line string instead of
   buffering it anywhere — each `writer.writerow(...)` call's return value
   (the freshly-formatted line) is yielded directly into the
   `StreamingResponse`. The DB query itself is also lazily iterated
   (`for paper, _decision in rows:` over a SQLModel `.exec()` result) rather
   than materialized into a list first. No full-CSV string is ever built
   in memory before wrapping — this is genuine row-at-a-time streaming, not
   the common false-streaming anti-pattern of building the whole body and
   handing it to StreamingResponse as one chunk.

